<H3>Xanadu</H3>

Ted Nelson, hypertext champion and pioneer, author of <I>Computer Lib</I> and
<I>Literary Machines</I> discusses the
<a href="http://xanadu.net/the.project">Xanadu</a> hypertext system and its
future, the recent Wired article, and gives advice for aspiring visionaries.
About half of this interview was transcribed for an article
in the Winter KUCI Program Guide titled
<A HREF="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~ejw/csr/nelson_pg.html"><I>Orality and
Hypertext: An Interview with Ted Nelson</I></a>.<P>

"What would I recommend to a young visionary today? {laughter} Very
straightforward, learn to live with short term goals and not delegate.
I trusted them {laughter, pause} famous last words ..."<P>

<DL>
<DT><A HREF="ftp://liege.ics.uci.edu/pub/ejw/nelson/nelson1.au">
