<H3>Virtual Communities</H3>

<a href="http://www.sscnet.ucla.edu/soc/grads/smithm/smithm.htm">
Marc Smith</a>, a fourth-year doctoral student in the
<a href="http://www.sscnet.ucla.edu/soc/">Dept. of Sociology</a> at
U.C.L.A. discusses his paper,
<i><a href="http://www.sscnet.ucla.edu/soc/csoc/virtcomm.htm">Voices
From the WELL: The Logic of the Virtual Commons</a></i> about
<a href="http://www.sscnet.ucla.edu/soc/csoc/">virtual communities</a>
on the Well BBS.<p>

"It would be a mistake to say that in cyberspace you can't get hurt.
You can get hurt in cyberspace, and in ways you might not imagine."<p>

<DL>
<DT><A HREF="ftp://liege.ics.uci.edu/pub/ejw/smith/smith1.au">
